From: CCLRTE <cclrte@local>
Date: Mon, 21 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: select ARCH_SUPPORTS_RT to enable PREEMPT_RT

The RPi kernel fork dropped 'select ARCH_SUPPORTS_RT' from the arm64
config block that mainline Linux 6.6 has. Without it, CONFIG_PREEMPT_RT
has an unsatisfied dependency and merge_config.sh silently falls back to
CONFIG_PREEMPT=y (the defconfig default), making the PREEMPT_RT option
invisible in Kconfig and unusable via .cfg fragments.

This one-line addition restores parity with mainline arm64 Kconfig,
allowing CONFIG_PREEMPT_RT=y in cclrte-rt.cfg to take effect.

Signed-off-by: CCLRTE <cclrte@local>
---
 arch/arm64/Kconfig | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/Kconfig b/arch/arm64/Kconfig
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/arm64/Kconfig
@@ -89,6 +89,7 @@ config ARM64
 	select ARCH_SUPPORTS_HUGETLBFS
 	select ARCH_SUPPORTS_MEMORY_FAILURE
 	select ARCH_SUPPORTS_SHADOW_CALL_STACK if CC_HAVE_SHADOW_CALL_STACK
+	select ARCH_SUPPORTS_RT
 	select ARCH_SUPPORTS_LTO_CLANG if CPU_LITTLE_ENDIAN
 	select ARCH_SUPPORTS_LTO_CLANG_THIN
 	select ARCH_SUPPORTS_CFI_CLANG
